{"id":"degree-tn-8","label":"Degrees of Comparision (TN-8)","lockAfter":3,"list":[{"type":"rightOne","id":"find-degree","label":"Right Degree","lockAfter":1,"commonData":{"title":"Identify the degree of the below word","hasHint":true,"fontSize":"1.5rem","hintFontSize":"2.5rem"},"data":["fast | Positive | Comparative | Superlative\ntallest | Superlative | Positive | Comparative \nsmaller |  Comparative | Superlative | Positive\npoorest | Superlative | Positive | Comparative \nweak | Positive | Comparative | Superlative\nricher |  Comparative | Superlative | Positive","smart | Positive | Comparative | Superlative\nsmartest | Superlative | Positive | Comparative \nsmarter |  Comparative | Superlative | Positive\nlatest | Superlative | Positive | Comparative \nlate | Positive | Comparative | Superlative\nlater |  Comparative | Superlative | Positive"]},{"type":"rightOne","id":"find-word","label":"Right Word for degree","lockAfter":1,"commonData":{"title":"Identify the word for the given degree","hasHint":true,"fontSize":"1.5rem","hintFontSize":"2.5rem"},"data":["Positive | fast | faster | fastest\nComparative |  longer | long | longest\nSuperlative | tallest | tall | taller \nComparative | larger | large | largest \nPositive | wide | wider | widest","Positive | large | larger | largest\nComparative |  quieter | quiet | quietest\nSuperlative | best | better | good\nComparative | hotter | hot | hottest\nComparative | more | many | most\nSuperlative | least | less | little"]},{"label":"Pick the Right Word","id":"complete","type":"completePuzzle","lockAfter":1,"commonData":{"type":"rightOpen","title":"Drag and drop the right word to form a hyphenated compound word.","printTitle":"Pick the right word to form a hyphenated compound word.","leftWidth":160,"rightWidth":200},"data":[{"title":"Match the right comparative degree for the given positive degree.","text":"big, bigger, biger\nhot, hotter, hoter\nhappy, happier, happyer\npretty, prettier, prettyer\ntall, taller, taler\nfast, faster, fastar\ncheap, cheaper, cheapar"},{"title":"Match the right comparative degree for the given positive degree.","text":"fast, faster, fastest\ntall, taller, tallest\nsmall, smaller, smallest\nstrong, stronger, strongest\nrich, richer, richest\npoor, poorer, poorest\nweak, weaker, weakest"},{"title":"Match the right comparative degree for the given positive degree.","text":"good, better, best\nbad, worse, worst\nlittle, less, least\nfar, farther, farthest\nlate, later, latest\nmuch, more , most"},{"title":"Match the right superlative degree for the given positive degree.","text":"fast, fastest, faster\ntall, tallest, taller\nsmall, smallest, smaller\nstrong, strongest, stronger\nrich, richest, richer\npoor, poorest, poorer\nweak, weakest, weaker"},{"title":"Match the right superlative degree for the given positive degree.","text":"good, best, better\nbad, worst, worse\nlittle, least, less\nfar, farthest, farther\nlate, latest, later\nmuch, most, more "}]},{"type":"makeSentence","label":"Make Sentence","id":"make-sentence","data":{"title":"Drag & Drop the words from the bottom and construct the sentence.","extras":" ","text":"Which is faster? A train or a plane? | A plane is faster than a train\nWhich is cheaper? Gold or Silver? | Silver is cheaper than Gold\nWhich is larger? City or village? | city is larger than village\nWhich is bigger? A sea or an ocean? | an ocean is bigger than a sea\nWhich is taller? A giraffe or a camel? | a giraffe is taller than a camel "}},{"label":"Fill in the blanks","type":"matchByDragDrop","id":"drag-drop","lockAfter":1,"commonData":{"title":"Fill in the blanks using suitable adjective."},"data":["City is not a *quiet* place.\nTown is *quieter* than a city.\nVillage is the *quietest* place.\nIstanbul is a *populated* city.\nMoscow is *more* populated than Istanbul.\nLondon is the *most* populated city.","Rainy weather is *good*.\nWindy weather is *better* than rainy weather.\nWarm weather is the *best* weather.\nA river is *deep*.\nA lake is *deeper* than a river.\nAn ocean is the *deepest* of all.","Spain is a *large* country.\nThe USA is *larger* than Spain.\nRussia is the *largest* country.\nThe Cauvery is a *long* river.\nThe Mahanadi is *longer* than the Cauvery.\nThe Ganga is the *longest* river.","Hyderabad is a *modern* city.\nChennai is *more* modern than Hyderabad.\nBengaluru is the *most* modern city.\nGoat is a *tall* animal.\nHorse is *taller* than goat.\nGiraffe is the *tallest* animal.","Cat is a *strong* animal.\nDog is *stronger* than cat.\nElephant is the *strongest* animal.\nTamilnadu is a *hot* place.\nMaharastra is *hotter* than Tamilnadu.\nRajasthan is the *hottest* of all states."]}]}